      "id": "151e4db6-1239-8089-af91-dae9e24f9548",
      "type": "heading_2",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "1. What is Statistics Calculator?",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-809d-b60a-dca51cda29d6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "A statistics calculator is a powerful tool designed to handle and analyze data. It helps in understanding the characteristics and patterns within a set of numbers. Whether you're dealing with a small set of data like the scores of a class test or a large dataset such as population statistics, this calculator can perform various operations. It can calculate measures of central tendency like the mean, median, and mode, which give an idea of where the \"center\" of the data lies. It also computes measures of dispersion such as the standard deviation and variance, which tell us how spread out the data is. In short, a statistics calculator simplifies the complex task of data analysis and provides valuable insights.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
