    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-8060-92c6-de1933a1ceec",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The standard deviation ",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "s\\ ",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "is the square root of the variance, so ",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "s=\\sqrt{s^{2}}",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "\nFormula Explanation: It gives a more interpretable measure of the spread of data compared to the variance.\nCase Application: Using the variance ",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "s^{2}=10",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": " from the previous example.\nSolution:\nAnswer: The standard deviation of the data set is approximately \\(3.16\\).",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
