    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-803a-a682-f170586c66cb",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "3.5 Covariance Formula",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80ce-a4db-c8112372ca90",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The formula for the covariance between two variables \\(X\\) and \\(Y\\) is:\n\\[\nCov(X,Y)=\\frac{\\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_{i}-\\bar{x})(y_{i}-\\bar{y})}{n - 1}\n\\]\nFormula Explanation: It measures the relationship between two variables, indicating how they vary together.\nCase Application: Let \\(X=\\{1, 2, 3\\}\\) with mean \\(\\bar{x}=2\\) and \\(Y=\\{4, 5, 6\\}\\) with mean \\(\\bar{y}=5\\)\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\nCov(X,Y)&=\\frac{(1-2)(4 - 5)+(2-2)(5-5)+(3-2)(6-5)}{3-1}\\\\\n&=\\frac{1+0+1}{2}\\\\\n&=1\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\nAnswer: The covariance between \\(X\\) and \\(Y\\) is \\(1\\).",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
