    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80c4-bd55-c11543b67291",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Example 1: Business Sales Analysis",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-8069-a198-c08e8ad37406",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "A company has the following sales figures (in thousands of dollars) for the last 6 months: {12, 15, 18, 13, 17, 14}. Calculate the mean and standard deviation.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80a8-b568-fce4179ca182",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Solution:\nMean:\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n\\bar{x}&=\\frac{12+15+18+13+17+14}{6}\\\\\n&=\\frac{89}{6}\\approx14.83\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\nVariance:\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\ns^{2}&=\\frac{(12-14.83)^{2}+(15-14.83)^{2}+(18-14.83)^{2}+(13-14.83)^{2}+(17-14.83)^{2}+(14-14.83)^{2}}{6-1}\\\\\n&=\\frac{7.9889+0.0289+9.9889+3.3489+4.6689+0.6889}{5}\\\\\n&=\\frac{26.7134}{5}\\approx5.34\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\nStandard Deviation: \\(s=\\sqrt{5.34}\\approx2.31\\)\nAnswer: The mean is approximately \\(14.83\\) thousand dollars and the standard deviation is approximately \\(2.31\\) thousand dollars.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80e5-9b61-fffedea85603",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Example 2: Student Grades Analysis",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-808d-99b9-fc6a168187d5",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In a class, the test scores of 8 students are {75, 80, 90, 65, 70, 85, 95, 78}. Find the median and mode.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-8025-874c-e8eb193354c1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Solution:\nFirst, we sort the data set: {65, 70, 75, 78, 80, 85, 90, 95}\nMedian: Since \\(n = 8\\) (even), the median is the average of the \\(\\frac{8}{2}^{th}\\) and \\(\\left(\\frac{8}{2}+ 1\\right)^{th}\\) values, which is \\(\\frac{78+80}{2}=79\\)\nMode: There is no mode as each value appears only once.\nAnswer: The median is \\(79\\) and there is no mode.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-8089-a52e-f68cf1659ed9",
      "type": "heading_3",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Example 3: Environmental Data Analysis",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80d5-af89-f4895b97fa85",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The following are the daily temperature readings (in degrees Celsius) for a week: {20, 22, 23, 19, 21, 24, 20}. Calculate the variance.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "151e4db6-1239-80f3-bbde-f9a6d0311bec",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Solution:\nMean:\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n\\bar{x}&=\\frac{20+22+23+19+21+24+20}{7}\\\\\n&=\\frac{149}{7}\\approx21.29\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\nVariance:\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\ns^{2}&=\\frac{(20-21.29)^{2}+(22-21.29)^{2}+(23-21.29)^{2}+(19-21.29)^{2}+(21-21.29)^{2}+(24-21.29)^{2}+(20-21.29)^{2}}{7-1}\\\\\n&=\\frac{1.6641+0.4961+2.9241+5.2441+0.0841+7.3961+1.6641}{6}\\\\\n&=\\frac{19.4727}{6}\\approx3.25\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\nAnswer: The variance is approximately \\(3.25\\) degrees Celsius squared.",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
